{"cursor":"10155","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Card manipulation' is the branch of magical illusion that deals with creating\neffects using sleight of hand techniques involving playing cards. Card\nmanipulation is often used in magical performances, especially in close-up,\nparlor, and street magic. Some of the most recognized names in this field\ninclude Dai Vernon, Ed Marlo, and Alex Elmsley. Before becoming world famous for\nhis escapes, Houdini billed himself as \"The King of Cards\".\n","linknr":277,"url":"Card_manipulation","recorded":1362574556,"links":23,"instances":["gambling","illusion","cards"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Card magic|","Circus skills","Card tricks"],"headings":["History","Technique","Example","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Card_trick.jpg/220px-Card_trick.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/Crystal_Clear_app_Startup_Wizard.png/80px-Crystal_Clear_app_Startup_Wizard.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["magic","illusion"],["cut","cards"],["crimp","gambling"]],"members":["crimp","magic","cut"],"related":["Magic_(illusion)","Sleight_of_hand","Playing_card","Close-up_magic","Parlor_magic","Street_magic","Dai_Vernon","Ed_Marlo","Alex_Elmsley","Houdini","Sleight_of_hand","Cups_and_balls","Martin_Gardner","The_Expert_at_the_Card_Table","Sleight_of_hand","Second_dealing","Bottom_dealing","Palming","Shuffling","Cut_(cards)","Crimp_(gambling)","Derek_Dingle","Michael_Ammar","Card_marking","Sleight_of_hand","Trick_deck","Card_flourish","Card_throwing","Card_sharp"]